cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.CY 

This paper deals with detecting internet filtering, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The approach proposed in the paper involves analyzing time series data, which is a common technique in networked systems (cs.NI) and data science (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of circumvention tools, which could be considered a form of cyber activism (cs.CY). Finally, the paper evaluates the sensitivity of the technique against different classes of censorship events, which could be seen as a form of statistical inference (cs.SI).
